                                   GLOCaml
                                 Issac Trotts 
                            <ijtrotts@ucdavis.edu>
                                     2003

Introduction
============
GLOCaml, pronounced "glow camel", is a simple binding of OpenGL for OCaml,
using Xavier Leroy's wrapper generator Camlidl.

Comparison of GL wrappers for OCaml
===================================

________________________________|_LablGL_|_camlgl______|_GLOCaml_|
Easy man page lookup?           | no     | yes         | yes     |
Easy conversion of C demos?     | no     | yes         | yes     |
OCaml knowledge required        | *1     | basic       | basic   |
OpenGL version(s) supported     | 1.1    | 1.2         | 1.2     |
Includes GLU bindings           | yes    | no          | yes     |
Includes GLUT bindings          | yes*2  | ~partial*3  | no*     |
-----------------------------------------------------------------+

*1 Requires knowledge of polymorphic variants, labeled function arguments, and
  optional function arguments. 
*2 LablGLUT is now included with LablGL.
*3 camlgl's glut wrapper doesn't appear to support multiple windows.
*4 It should be easy to use LablGLUT or OCamlSDL with GLOCaml.  
   OCamlSDL is the cleaner and more powerful choice.

Installation
============
    ./config.sh
    make
    make install

